# ralph-accounts.example.env — multi-account usage failover for ralph-watchdog.sh
#
# WHAT THIS IS
#   When the ACTIVE Claude account hits its subscription usage cap mid-loop, the
#   watchdog ends that iteration cleanly, switches to the NEXT account here,
#   exhausts that one too, and — when ALL accounts are capped — sleeps until the
#   soonest one's usage window resets, then resumes automatically. With NO
#   accounts file at all, the loop runs on your ambient keychain login and STILL
#   detects the cap and waits for reset (it just can't fail over to another login).
#
# HOW TO USE
#   1. Copy this file to .ralph/accounts.env   (that path is gitignored — NEVER
#      commit real tokens):
#         cp scripts/ralph-accounts.example.env .ralph/accounts.env
#   2. For EACH Claude login you want in the rotation, generate a long-lived
#      OAuth token on that login:
#         claude setup-token
#      Paste the token into RALPH_ACCT_<N>_TOKEN below.
#   3. Set RALPH_ACCT_COUNT to how many accounts you've filled in.
#
# NOTES
#   - Tokens stay shell-local to the watchdog; only the single ACTIVE account's
#     CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN is exported per iteration.
#   - RALPH_ACCT_<N>_CONFIG_DIR is OPTIONAL: point it at a separate
#     CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR per account if you want fully isolated config/state per
#     login. Leave blank to use the default config dir.
#   - An account whose _TOKEN is blank is skipped (treated as not configured).

# How many accounts are defined below (count the ones with a real token).
RALPH_ACCT_COUNT=0

# ---- Account 1 ----
RALPH_ACCT_1_LABEL="primary"
RALPH_ACCT_1_TOKEN=""
RALPH_ACCT_1_CONFIG_DIR=""

# ---- Account 2 ----
RALPH_ACCT_2_LABEL="secondary"
RALPH_ACCT_2_TOKEN=""
RALPH_ACCT_2_CONFIG_DIR=""

# ---- Account 3 (add more by copying this block and bumping the index) ----
RALPH_ACCT_3_LABEL="tertiary"
RALPH_ACCT_3_TOKEN=""
RALPH_ACCT_3_CONFIG_DIR=""
